answers.body_markdown:
I think it is better if you have ManyToMany relation between products and categories.

https://laravel.com/docs/5.8/eloquent-relationships#many-to-many

    class Product extends Model
    {
        
        public function categories()
        {
            return $this-&gt;belongsToMany(&#39;App\categories&#39;);
        }
    }

With that in mind, it would be a lot easier. 

    $product = App\Product::find(1);
    foreach ($product-&gt;categories as $category) {
         //
    }

You have many categories and many products.
Each product will have many categories, and many categories will have many products. Instead of having one row with multiple categories, you will have multiple rows with one product and one category. You can add an extra column in the pivot table if you want to add the subcategory type.

